# Sanity CMS

One shared Sanity project/dataset powers all apps. Content is separated per country via a
`market` field — this is the backbone of the multi-market architecture.

## Rules

- **Every market-scoped document type MUST include the `market` field** — spread in
  `marketField` from `@odyssey/cms` (`src/schema/market-field.ts`). Add new markets to
  `MARKETS` in `src/types.ts`.
- **Every content query MUST filter on `market`.** Use `fetchByMarket(type, market, ...)` or
  include `market == $market` in GROQ. Never return cross-market content to an app.
- Register new schemas in `src/schema/index.ts`.
- Keep the read client (`sanityClient`) and schema definitions separate: apps import from
  `@odyssey/cms`; the studio imports `@odyssey/cms/schema`.
- Type all query results; don't return `any` from GROQ fetches.
- Config comes from env (`NEXT_PUBLIC_SANITY_*`); never hard-code project id/dataset.
